net.novazero.lib.ikbus.util

Class ByteArrayByteString

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.novazero.lib.ikbus.util.ByteArrayByteString
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Byte>, ByteString

    public class ByteArrayByteString
extends Object
implements Iterable<Byte>, ByteString
    An immutable sequence of bytes. This class can be used as a lightweight wrapper for byte arrays to guarantee read only access to the data.
    Author:
    Daan Scheerens

    • Constructor Detail

      • ByteArrayByteString

        public ByteArrayByteString(byte[] bytes)
        Creates a new ByteArrayByteString from the specified byte array. Note that the byte array will be cloned in order to prevent external mutation of the array.
        Parameters:
        bytes - An array of bytes that serves as the source data for the ByteArrayByteString.

      • ByteArrayByteString

        public ByteArrayByteString(byte[] bytes,
                           boolean cloneArray)
        Creates a new ByteArrayByteString from the specified byte array. The cloneArray parameter controls whether a clone is made of the given byte array. In general it is recommended to do so as this guarantees immutability. However, if you are certain that the given array will not be modified outside the scope of this class, then it safe to use the original array. In that case you can pass false as an argument for the cloneArray parameter.
        Parameters:
        bytes - An array of bytes that serves as the source data for the ByteArrayByteString.
        cloneArray - Whether the array should be cloned to ensure immutability.
